-- MOVES-Armstrong Investment names Christopher Sullivan director
-- 
-- Wed Dec 03, 2014 06:52AM EST
-- None



Dec 3 (Reuters) - Armstrong Investment Managers appointed Christopher Sullivan director and head of distribution, effective immediately.

Sullivan will be responsible for establishing sales teams in Europe, the Middle East and the United States, the London-based company said.  Most recently, he co-founded European Capital Markets, an independent consultancy focused on providing alternative investment managers access to capital.